node.text: my nipz are closing shows at NYFW 🌱 i’m literally crying this is a dream come true mama i made it to the runway!!! urban plants. a collection celebrating green! presenting the positive effects on community and mental health. @privatepolicyny asked me to embody mother earth. a goddess sent to warn humanity to change our ways and appreciate the fruit of the world. this was a PERFORMANCE and pushed me out of my comfort zone... i am so honored to have been asked to close the show! ASIAN REPRESENTATION is here baby. Siyinq Qi it was an honor. seeing so many trans & asian models backstage made me so emotional! i’m so proud to be apart of the movement.

node.text:
good morning bad bitch... this is ur daily reminder that ur a bad bitch. and if ANYONE has anything else to say send them a signed copy of ur magazine cover 💅thank u @fault_magazine for this months cover! some have have effort and some have less. effortless comes from being authentically u and baby if there’s one thing i’m gonna do is be me. trusting ur intuition and talent is so hard... especially as a woman. ain’t dimming down my shine for no one! and u better NOT either... get out ur own way hoe. 
styled by @joeythao 
make up by @erosmua 
hair by @rikkigash

node.text: HELLO GRINCHES 🤗💚 new york city i’m back baby! post panoramic i’ve missed u so... my senior year of high school my queerass was supposed to run away to performing arts college in nyc. i knew in that moment if i went down that path i would NEVER become the woman i’ve always wanted to be... i was sooo good at acting cus i acted like a boy for 18 years of my life. that nyc east coast energy left me and honestly is what made me thrive in hollywood. TAG a bestie and let em know they the baddest 🔫🐲

node.text:
Empress Dragun 🐉 Queen of Social Media. powerful asian women are typically defined as the villain or a weird type of fetish. with this cover i wanted to embody the power of my own truth being a poc female without interpretation. taking away the stereotype. i’m proud to be ASIAN. more than that i’m proud to look asian. my reign as the mother of draguns has just begun... what scares people about my femininity is that i cary it like a man. it takes a lot of balls be a powerful woman... i should know ;) thank u @kingkongmagazine for the cover and my amazing haus of dragun team!
stylist: @joeythao
makeup: @makeupbyariel 
hair: @fitchlunarhair 
photographer: @mayafuhr 
set design: @itsisaacaaron 
wearing: @maisonvalentino @laureldewitt

node.text: God, thank u. u have given me many roles in this life and none i take more seriously than God Father. my beautiful niece Eva is my everything and grounds me to not being as reckless knowing i have a responsibility to her forever... and yes i said God Father. i told my family that god mother makes me sound like an old fairy lady... but God Father makes me sounds like a boss. this is gonna be a fun one for Baby Eva to have to explain one day... i know it might be confusing to y’all and u might not get it. but u don’t have to. this is for me and my family. i’m Tia Nina and God Father Dragun.
